webpackJsonp([39669513714384],{557:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{wordpressWpLessons:{id:"dae42295-baee-595e-92c5-28d1ed051eaf",wordpress_id:6705,title:"Web Development Mini Project",slug:"web-development-mini-project",content:'<h2>Project Overview</h2>\n<p>Now that you&#8217;ve built your skills, let&#8217;s practice by creating an <em>About Me</em> page with <a href="http://mozilla.thimble.org">Thimble</a>! You may have already started this project but be sure to include everything that is listed in the <strong>project requirements</strong> section.</p>\n<h2>Project Prompt: <strong>Create an About Me Page</strong></h2>\n<p><strong><span style="color: #cf0000;">IMPORTANT: Please read this ENTIRE section before starting!</span></strong></p>\n<p>Using Thimble, design an <em>About Me</em> page that includes the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>HTML</strong><strong>:</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>An image of yourself with an <em>alt</em> tag included</li>\n<li>At least <strong>two</strong> lists:\n<ul>\n<li>1 list should be an <strong>ordered list</strong></li>\n<li>1 list should be an <strong>unordered list</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>At least <strong>two </strong>links</li>\n<li>Heading and paragraph elements\n<ul>\n<li>The content should be about yourself. Think about how you may want to structure the page and use headings to break up the text so that it&#8217;s more readable!</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>CSS:</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Functioning linked stylesheet.css</li>\n<li>Background color</li>\n<li>Text color</li>\n<li>One instance of a class or id being used\n<ul>\n<li>Remember, this needs to match the class or id used in HTML!</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You&#8217;re encouraged to add more content and to take your CSS skills further as well. If you do so, please make sure that your page meets the above requirements!</p>\n<h2>Maker&#8217;s Reflection</h2>\n<p>Take some screenshots and store them in the appropriate Google Drive folder!</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Login with your DHF email address if you aren&#8217;t already.</li>\n<li>Navigate to <a href="https://drive.google.com">Google Drive</a>. Since you&#8217;re already logged in with your email, you&#8217;ll be taken directly to your personal drive.</li>\n<li>Select <strong>My Drive</strong> from the left sidebar and open up the course drive folder.</li>\n<li>Locate (and click to open) your cohort folder and find (and open) the folder with your name on it.</li>\n<li>Open the <em>Web Development</em> folder</li>\n<li>Upload any screenshots to this folder</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Next, find the forum thread for the <em>Web Development Project</em>. Reply to that topic and answer these 3 questions in your reflection:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>What was the project prompt?</li>\n<li>What is your project?</li>\n<li>Why did you make this project?</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Then, choose at least 2 from the list below to respond to.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>How did you plan or prototype your project before starting?</li>\n<li>How did you make it? What was your process? What steps did you follow?</li>\n<li>What problems or challenges did you face?</li>\n<li>How did you overcome any challenges and solve problems that you met?</li>\n<li>What would you do differently next time?</li>\n<li>What would you tell someone else who was going to make this project?</li>\n<li>What did you like best about your project?</li>\n<li>How would you make it better?</li>\n</ul>\n'}},pathContext:{}}}});
